<anchor id="rms__store_8h_1rms_store"/> <simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>Acceleration measurement data provided by AXO X1 includes root mean square (RMS) values, hit values and a timestamp. The RMS storage provides a structure to held these values and reserves RAM to store for a configurable amount of time. <linebreak/>
The RMS and hit values will be calculated by RMS task and send via message to the RMS storage task (see header file <ref refid="rms_8h_1rms" kindref="member">rms</ref> (<ref refid="rms_8h" kindref="compound">rms.h</ref>)). <linebreak/>
For more details see also message sequence charts in section <ref refid="_m_s_c_1SectionMeasurement" kindref="member">Measurement</ref>.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="remark"><para>This source code is confidential and proprietary information of AXO Track GmbH, Berlin. You may not disclose, copy, or distribute this source code or any part thereof without the explicit permission of AXO Track GmbH, Berlin. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
